      "last_updated": "2026-07-08",
      "supersedes": null,
      "contradicted_by": null
    },
    {
      "text": "The Arabat Spit, located to the northeast, is a narrow strip of land that separates the Syvash lagoons from the Sea of Azov.",
      "source_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crimea",
      "source_type": "reference_work",
      "confidence_tier": "reported",
      "fact_id": "fct_002",
      "first_reported": "2026-07-08",
      "last_updated": "2026-07-08",
      "supersedes": null,
      "contradicted_by": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Across the Black Sea to the west lies Romania and to the south is Turkey.",
      "source_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crimea",
